# WaveLinux Notes

## Purpose

Quick technical orientation for contributors.

## Key files

- `main.py`: Qt UI and dialogs
- `pipewire_engine.py`: PipeWire routing, state, FX chain
- `wavelinux_theme.py`: stylesheet

## Runtime model

- User-space app only (no daemon/service)
- Uses subprocess tools: `pactl`, `pw-dump`, `wpctl`, `parec`
- State stored in `~/.config/wavelinux/config.json`

## Core behavior

- Two master buses: Monitor + Stream
- Stream bus exposed as `WaveLinux-Stream` for OBS
- Per-channel MON/STR controls
- App routing by resolved app identity with persistence
- Per-channel effects in one PipeWire filter-chain process
